<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3719] Pattern regex org.apache.kafka.common.utils.Utils.HOST_PORT_PATTERN is too narrow</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3719</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In our continuous integration environment the Kafka brokers run on hosts containing underscores in their names. The current regex splits incorrectly these names into host and port parts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I could submit a pull request if someone confirms that this is indeed a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12970417">KAFKA-3719</key>
            <summary>Pattern regex org.apache.kafka.common.utils.Utils.HOST_PORT_PATTERN is too narrow</summary>
